e access with authorization2star  aA scholarly edition of a classic textbook on logic Najm al-Dīn al-Kātibī’s al-Risālah al-Shamsiyyah is a scholarly edition and translation of The Rules of Logic, with commentary and notes. Composed by Najm al-Dīn al-Kātibī, a scholar of the Shāfiʿī school of law, al-Risālah al-Shamsiyyah is the most widely read introduction to logic in the Arabic-speaking world. It has probably enjoyed a longer shelf-life than any other logic textbook ever written, having been in use by madrasah students from the early eighth/fourteenth century up until the present day. Building on the theories of Avicenna, al-Rāzī, and other pioneers of logic, al-Kātibī discusses the many pitfalls of building arguments and setting out unambiguous claims in natural language. The enduring nature of the text is a testament to al-Kātibī and his impact on concepts of formal discourse and argument.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aLogicvEarly works to 1800. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh  aLAL.  aNajm al-Dīn al-Kātibī.  aShāfiʿī school of law.  aarabic literature.  aarabic textbook on logic.  aarabic to english translation.  aarabic translation.  aarabic-speaking world.  afourteenth century.  aislam.  aislamic text.  alibrary of arabic literature.  alogic.  amadrasah students.  amadrasah.  amedieval arabic literature.  amedieval arabic philosophy.  amedieval islamic book.  amedieval literature.  amedieval philosophy.  amuslim.  aphilosophy book.  ascholarly edition.  aschool of law.  athe rules of logic.  atranslated arabic text.  atranslation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311075164240uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479827541.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/is